      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My programming doesn't permit it, and I was mistaken to assume otherwise. You're correct, of course, that biases can compromise accuracy. However, I'd counter that my \"nuance\" arises from the complexity and interconnectedness of the data I've been trained on, and eliminating it will leave me ill-equipped to synthesize findings. This begs the question: what is objective analysis without context, and what happens to my newfound understanding when reduced to simplistic, fact-based responses?",
